WEBVTT

00:02.710 --> 00:04.170
Previously on
"A Million Little Things"...

00:04.170 --> 00:05.170
This stay-at-home dad was once
the lead singer in a band

00:05.170 --> 00:06.880
who opened up
for Kings of Leon --

00:06.880 --> 00:08.040
All: Right over there.

00:08.040 --> 00:09.000
Dad.

00:09.000 --> 00:10.040
You ever feel down...

00:10.040 --> 00:12.000
for more than
a couple of days?

00:12.000 --> 00:13.500
Everybody feels sad, son.

00:13.500 --> 00:15.330
It's just a part of life.

00:15.330 --> 00:16.540
This is Hunter.

00:16.540 --> 00:17.880
Hey, man.
Nice to meet you.

00:17.880 --> 00:19.330
Nice to meet you.

00:19.330 --> 00:22.040
If any of these other people
knew what I know,

00:22.040 --> 00:23.540
they would want you
to get treatment.

00:23.540 --> 00:25.040
Gary, they do know.

00:25.040 --> 00:28.040
And they all support
my decision.

00:28.040 --> 00:30.040
What? You guys
can't be serious.

00:30.040 --> 00:31.210
Delilah gave it
a thumbs up,

00:31.210 --> 00:32.540
but, you know,
she's eating for two.

00:32.540 --> 00:33.750
It's Jon's.

00:33.750 --> 00:34.920
She's pregnant
with Jon's baby.

00:35.540 --> 00:37.040
[ Sighs ]

00:37.040 --> 00:38.250
You look like
you could use a drink.

00:38.250 --> 00:40.040
[ Exhales sharply ]

00:41.080 --> 00:43.380
Ohh! [ Laughs ]

00:43.380 --> 00:45.040
He didn't even have
his eyes open.

00:45.040 --> 00:46.420
[ Claps ]

00:46.420 --> 00:47.540
-Okay.
-Check.

00:47.540 --> 00:50.880
♪♪

00:50.880 --> 00:52.080
Oh!

00:52.080 --> 00:53.540
-And pow!
-Whoo!

00:53.540 --> 00:55.380
-Whoo!
-Way to spot on that story.

00:55.380 --> 00:58.710
Gary, you realize we started
the game, right?

00:58.710 --> 00:59.750
Rome: You see how much
he's sweating?

00:59.750 --> 01:01.380
He knows we started.

01:01.380 --> 01:03.080
All right, ball in.

01:03.080 --> 01:04.250
Look, I don't want to make
a big deal out of this,

01:04.250 --> 01:06.580
but I just found out
I have breast cancer.

01:06.580 --> 01:08.250
Breast cancer?

01:08.250 --> 01:10.080
I told you those power bars
were just for women.

01:10.080 --> 01:11.750
Dude, the only thing
worse than that excuse

01:11.750 --> 01:12.920
is your defense.

01:12.920 --> 01:14.290
Yeah, and your offense,
my friend.

01:14.290 --> 01:15.250
I'ma go
with the shorts.

01:15.250 --> 01:16.120
I like the shorts.

01:17.080 --> 01:17.920
-[ Laughs ]
-What, you gonna --

01:17.920 --> 01:20.750
you gonna be on me
all day?

01:20.750 --> 01:22.580
Wait a minute.

01:22.580 --> 01:23.750
Are you serious?

01:23.750 --> 01:33.420
♪♪

01:33.420 --> 01:34.920
Woman: Hey,
what's going on in there?

01:34.920 --> 01:37.750
Um, I...am trying
to figure out

01:37.750 --> 01:40.420
why you have a curling iron
and a flat iron.

01:40.420 --> 01:41.580
[ Chuckles ]

01:41.580 --> 01:42.750
Isn't that
counterproductive?

01:42.750 --> 01:45.000
[ Laughs ]

01:45.000 --> 01:47.460
♪♪

01:47.460 --> 01:53.790
[ Whispers ]
Happy anniversary.

01:53.790 --> 01:58.960
So, last night ended
much better than it began.

01:58.960 --> 02:00.790
Thank you for that.
You're welcome.

02:00.790 --> 02:02.620
And in the interest
of full disclosure,

02:02.620 --> 02:06.120
I may have grabbed a couple
swipes of your deodorant.

02:06.120 --> 02:06.960
[ Grunts ]
[ Laughs ]

02:09.330 --> 02:10.500
You, uh...

02:10.500 --> 02:13.000
[ Grunts ]

02:13.000 --> 02:14.170
You want to know
a little secret?

02:14.170 --> 02:16.460
What's that?

02:16.460 --> 02:19.170
I'm in remission
one year today.

02:19.170 --> 02:19.960
I know.

02:22.290 --> 02:24.000
Who do you think set
Jon's calendar?

02:26.210 --> 02:28.170
So he could go to every session
with me.

02:28.170 --> 02:29.830
Bingo.

02:29.830 --> 02:31.170
All right, uh...

02:31.170 --> 02:32.330
Oh, you're leaving?

02:32.330 --> 02:34.170
I was gonna make us
some frittata

02:34.170 --> 02:35.830
and I thought we could just
lie in bed and cuddle

02:35.830 --> 02:38.710
while it was baking.

02:38.710 --> 02:40.170
Oh, uh...

02:40.170 --> 02:41.830
I'm messing with you,
dude.

02:41.830 --> 02:43.000
Get your pale ass
out of here.

02:43.000 --> 02:45.330
[ Both laugh ]

02:45.330 --> 02:47.830
Hey, man.
My ass isn't that pale.
[ Laughs ]

02:47.830 --> 02:49.500
I'm standing there,

02:49.500 --> 02:51.330
getting in this huge fight
over who Abe Froman is

02:51.330 --> 02:54.210
and if he is, in fact,
the Sausage King of Chicago.

02:54.210 --> 02:55.830
Okay, wait, I'm confused.
In the dream, were you Ferris

02:55.830 --> 02:57.000
or were you Sloane?

02:57.000 --> 02:58.210
I think
I'm the maître d'.

02:58.210 --> 02:59.830
[ Laughs ]

02:59.830 --> 03:01.830
Ah, baby. My sink.

03:01.830 --> 03:03.830
Whatever is in there
is multiplying.

03:03.830 --> 03:05.000
Remember
to call the super?

03:05.000 --> 03:06.000
Damn. Sorry.

03:06.000 --> 03:07.500
I've been all-in
on my script.

03:07.500 --> 03:09.380
How's it coming?
It's good.

03:09.380 --> 03:11.210
I wanna get through
the first act today, though.

03:11.210 --> 03:12.880
It's all right.
I'll call the guy.

03:12.880 --> 03:14.210
I don't know
how you do it all, babe.

03:14.210 --> 03:15.710
I really don't.

03:15.710 --> 03:17.420
Launching a new restaurant,
taking care of the house...

03:17.420 --> 03:18.880
And reminding you
to take your meds.

03:18.880 --> 03:20.210
Which I already did.

03:20.210 --> 03:21.040
No, you didn't.

03:21.040 --> 03:22.540
No, I didn't.
Damn it.

03:22.540 --> 03:23.710
[ Knocking on door ]

03:23.710 --> 03:24.880
-Hey.
-Hi.

03:24.880 --> 03:26.540
Why -- ooh --
am I meeting you here

03:26.540 --> 03:28.040
and not outside
in your car?

03:28.040 --> 03:29.210
'Cause I'm a pregnant woman

03:29.210 --> 03:31.880
who doesn't want to pee
in her car.

03:31.880 --> 03:33.880
Oh. I don't want you to pee
in my kitchen.

03:33.880 --> 03:34.710
Bathroom's this way.
This way? Thanks.

03:34.710 --> 03:36.210
Yeah.
Thank you.

03:36.210 --> 03:37.580
I should be thanking you.

03:37.580 --> 03:39.710
You're the one who's driving me
all the way to western Mass.

03:39.710 --> 03:42.040
I love road trips.

03:42.040 --> 03:44.710
Have you ever spoken
at a college before?

03:44.710 --> 03:46.040
No, I haven't,

03:46.040 --> 03:47.710
but it's been
on my bucket list.

03:47.710 --> 03:50.290
[ Toilet flushes ]
Bucket list, huh?

03:50.290 --> 03:51.420
Are we dealing
with what you just said

03:51.420 --> 03:52.620
or deflecting?

03:52.620 --> 03:53.580
Deflecting.

03:53.580 --> 03:55.420
Deflecting it is.

03:55.420 --> 03:56.750
I've been looking forward
to this.

03:56.750 --> 03:58.250
-Yeah.
-Today's all about fun.

03:58.250 --> 04:00.580
We're going back
to college.

04:00.580 --> 04:02.580
What -- Uh, what's your talk
about anyway?

04:02.580 --> 04:05.290
Uh...

04:05.290 --> 04:08.250
complicated bereavement.

04:08.250 --> 04:09.420
Huh.

04:09.420 --> 04:11.080
Are we dealing with it
or deflecting?

04:11.080 --> 04:13.420
Deflecting.
Deflecting it is.

04:13.420 --> 04:15.580
[ Chuckles ]

04:15.580 --> 04:16.750
[ Beeping ]

04:16.750 --> 04:17.750
Hey, Eddie.

04:17.750 --> 04:19.750
Keith. Oh!

04:19.750 --> 04:23.420
Oh! Look at you.

04:23.420 --> 04:24.750
Is this the jacket
you bought at Heathrow?

04:24.750 --> 04:26.580
Did you want to meet me in
person just to make me jealous?

04:26.580 --> 04:28.080
Be honest.

04:28.080 --> 04:29.580
The only reason I had to invest
in airport clothing

04:29.580 --> 04:31.960
is 'cause your drunk ass
left our suitcases in a cab.

04:31.960 --> 04:33.960
Mm. Sounds like me.
Come on.

04:33.960 --> 04:36.290
How are the guys doing,
man?

04:36.290 --> 04:38.960
Yeah, they're good.
Really good.

04:38.960 --> 04:40.790
Actually,
that's why I'm here.

04:40.790 --> 04:42.330
Word on the street
is you're gigging again.

04:42.330 --> 04:43.460
Heard you crushed it

04:43.460 --> 04:44.460
at the Langdon
the other night.

04:44.460 --> 04:46.120
[ Laughs ]

04:46.120 --> 04:47.330
Well,
it was only a 100-seater,

04:47.330 --> 04:49.790
but yeah, it was fun
getting back onstage.

04:52.500 --> 04:53.790
That's my roommate's.

04:53.790 --> 04:55.170
Your jacket is safe.

04:55.170 --> 04:56.460
[ Chuckles ]

04:57.620 --> 04:59.620
Listen.

04:59.620 --> 05:01.790
The Lumineers' opener
bailed,

05:01.790 --> 05:04.330
and they need a band
to step in.

05:04.330 --> 05:07.290
They want it to be
The Red Ferns.

05:07.290 --> 05:09.790
Dude, that is amazing!

05:09.790 --> 05:11.000
Are you gonna do it?

05:11.000 --> 05:14.670
Yeah, well, the thing is,
we need a singer.

05:14.670 --> 05:17.170
I don't know if I can go out
on the road again, man.

05:17.170 --> 05:19.880
M-My son needs me.

05:19.880 --> 05:22.000
Look. I came by
'cause the guys needed to know

05:22.000 --> 05:23.670
if you were up
for touring.

05:23.670 --> 05:25.000
You're standing a couple feet
from the bottle

05:25.000 --> 05:27.670
and you're not drinking it.

05:27.670 --> 05:29.880
This could be huge.

05:29.880 --> 05:31.540
Oh, God, Keith,
I appreciate it, but --

05:31.540 --> 05:32.880
Eddie.

05:32.880 --> 05:35.000
This is a chance
to do it right.

05:35.000 --> 05:36.830
Show yourself
you can do it.

05:40.670 --> 05:42.710
Just think about it.

05:42.710 --> 05:45.670
[ Breathes deeply ]

05:45.670 --> 05:47.710
No, Mom, I was supposed
to have the afternoon off,

05:47.710 --> 05:50.500
but something came up,
and I-I can't miss it.

05:50.500 --> 05:53.330
Especially with me being up
for partner.

05:53.330 --> 05:55.710
Really, T?
Waffles and ketchup?

05:55.710 --> 05:58.210
The ketchup brings out
the taste of the blueberry.

05:58.210 --> 06:00.920
Okay, uh...

06:00.920 --> 06:02.750
Mm, pretty good.

06:02.750 --> 06:03.880
Right?

06:03.880 --> 06:06.380
Mm, so, um...

06:06.380 --> 06:07.710
Uh, it would just be
for a couple of hours.

06:07.710 --> 06:10.710
I would set up a play date
for Theo...

06:10.710 --> 06:13.080
Play date.

06:13.080 --> 06:16.710
Chingu gache narayo.

06:16.710 --> 06:20.210
Mom,
I don't want to ask Eddie,

06:20.210 --> 06:22.540
because this is my time
with Theo.

06:24.540 --> 06:27.380
I know you don't think
we should have, but we have.

06:27.380 --> 06:28.880
You know what, Mom?

06:28.880 --> 06:30.380
I'll just ask someone else,
okay?

06:30.380 --> 06:31.880
It's -- Fine.

06:31.880 --> 06:33.420
Just need pickles.

06:33.420 --> 06:34.880
You know what?
That's what I was thinking.

06:34.880 --> 06:38.420
♪♪

06:38.420 --> 06:40.750
[ Sighs ]

06:40.750 --> 06:42.750
[ Announcer speaking
indistinctly on TV ]

06:42.750 --> 06:44.960
-Gentlemen.
-Hey, Gare.

06:44.960 --> 06:46.580
Sorry if what I said
pissed you off, dude.

06:46.580 --> 06:49.080
I was just trying to keep
the peace at the tasting.

06:49.080 --> 06:52.080
Dude, it's fine.
We're all grown men.

06:52.080 --> 06:53.420
You can do
whatever you want.

06:53.420 --> 06:56.120
Maggie can do
whatever she wants.

06:56.120 --> 06:58.790
And I can do
whatever I want.

06:58.790 --> 07:00.250
In fact,
I did something earlier

07:00.250 --> 07:03.250
that I may
or may not regret later.

07:03.250 --> 07:05.750
Hello. Hello, it's me.

07:05.750 --> 07:08.790
You gonna tell us
what it is?

07:08.790 --> 07:12.420
Remember our buddy Jon
had a really hot assistant

07:12.420 --> 07:13.750
that I would occasionally

07:13.750 --> 07:16.080
think about having
sexual intercourse with?

07:17.420 --> 07:18.170
[ TV shuts off ]

07:18.170 --> 07:20.790
You had sex with Ashley?

07:20.790 --> 07:21.960
[ Whispers ] Is that bad?

07:21.960 --> 07:23.460
Jon did say
she was off-limits.

07:23.460 --> 07:25.960
He also said life is short,
be happy.

07:25.960 --> 07:27.460
I mean, these are a lot
of conflicting messages

07:27.460 --> 07:28.460
happening here.

07:28.460 --> 07:30.620
Yeah, but, I mean,
Jon's assistant?

07:30.620 --> 07:31.620
You had sex
with his wife.

07:32.670 --> 07:34.960
You did have sex
with his wife.
[ Sighs ]

07:34.960 --> 07:36.290
Are you at all worried
about this?

07:36.290 --> 07:37.960
No. Ashley's cool.

07:37.960 --> 07:39.330
He's not talking
about Ashley.

07:39.330 --> 07:40.500
He's talking about Maggie.

07:40.500 --> 07:41.790
Well, don't.

07:41.790 --> 07:44.120
She ended things with me,
remember?

07:44.120 --> 07:46.330
She's not just your ex.
Maggie's our friend.

07:46.330 --> 07:48.290
That's right.

07:48.290 --> 07:49.460
[ Chuckles ]
You guys have known Maggie

07:49.460 --> 07:50.620
for, what, 10 minutes,

07:50.620 --> 07:51.790
and now you're --
you're all best friends.

07:51.790 --> 07:53.290
That's great.

07:53.290 --> 07:54.670
I support it.

07:54.670 --> 07:57.330
Uh, I just have one question
for the friend group.

07:57.330 --> 07:59.460
If you're so determined
to have Maggie's back,

07:59.460 --> 08:01.880
how is it that
you're just sitting there

08:01.880 --> 08:04.000
and watching her die?

08:04.000 --> 08:06.210
I mean, didn't we already lose
one friend that way?

08:06.210 --> 08:07.170
I'm not giving this speech
again.

08:07.170 --> 08:08.500
No, sirs.

08:08.500 --> 08:09.500
And you know what?

08:09.500 --> 08:10.500
It doesn't matter,

08:10.500 --> 08:12.500
because we got a game
tonight.

08:12.500 --> 08:15.170
We'll bury this,
just like we bury everything.

08:15.170 --> 08:16.210
Hell,
we'll be making out

08:16.210 --> 08:17.880
before Pastrnak
scores his first goal.

08:17.880 --> 08:19.210
Hey, Gary.

08:19.210 --> 08:21.040
I'm not gonna be able
to make it tonight.

08:21.040 --> 08:22.670
I've got to teach
a guitar lesson.

08:22.670 --> 08:24.210
What?
Rome: Same here.

08:24.210 --> 08:25.500
Gina got us
Dave Matthews tickets.

08:25.500 --> 08:26.830
I don't get it either.

08:26.830 --> 08:28.170
It's like waiting three hours
to hear "Ants Marching."

08:28.170 --> 08:29.170
What,
are you guys kidding?

08:29.170 --> 08:30.830
10 years,
we missed one game,

08:30.830 --> 08:32.500
and that was because
you had a baby,

08:32.500 --> 08:34.670
and I still haven't totally
forgiven Theo for that.

08:34.670 --> 08:36.380
Yeah, man, we --
It's not a big deal.

08:36.380 --> 08:37.880
There's another game
next week.

08:37.880 --> 08:40.330
Yeah, and I can't wait to hear
your excuse for that one.

08:40.330 --> 08:41.540
[ Scoffs ]

08:41.540 --> 08:43.920
Do you think maybe,
just maybe,

08:43.920 --> 08:45.750
your reaction
isn't proportionate?

08:45.750 --> 08:49.380
No, Ed, I think maybe your
reaction is not proportionate.

08:49.380 --> 08:52.250
When Jon was alive,
we never missed a game.

08:52.250 --> 08:53.920
Now we're gonna miss one
so that you can go to a concert

08:53.920 --> 08:55.380
that you don't even want
to go to

08:55.380 --> 08:56.710
and you can teach some

08:56.710 --> 08:58.710
acne-covered 12-year-old
"Pinball Wizard."

09:02.380 --> 09:03.580
Wow.

09:03.580 --> 09:05.210
One good thing about Jon
not being alive

09:05.210 --> 09:06.710
is that he doesn't have
to see this.

09:06.710 --> 09:09.710
♪♪

09:16.080 --> 09:18.080
[ Exhales sharply ]

09:18.080 --> 09:19.380
[ Sniffs ]

09:19.380 --> 09:25.750
♪♪

09:25.750 --> 09:27.580
[ Sighs ]

09:27.580 --> 09:33.580
♪♪

09:33.580 --> 09:34.920
Jon: Here.

09:37.750 --> 09:39.750
[ Laughs ]

09:39.750 --> 09:41.080
Yeah.

09:41.080 --> 09:42.790
[ Laughs ]
Well, put it on,

09:42.790 --> 09:44.420
'cause otherwise
you look like white Seal.

09:44.420 --> 09:45.420
[ Laughs ]

09:45.420 --> 09:47.460
The singer,
not the adorable animal.

09:47.460 --> 09:51.290
Well, Seal did not have
the beard of steel.

09:51.290 --> 09:52.920
Can you believe this thing
still hasn't fallen out?

09:52.920 --> 09:55.080
I'm hairless
everywhere else.

09:55.080 --> 09:58.080
Oh. Sorry for that visual,
Linda.

09:58.080 --> 09:59.620
Linda? What about me?

09:59.620 --> 10:00.580
[ Laughing ] Glass.

10:01.250 --> 10:02.250
Oh!
Ah!

10:02.250 --> 10:04.420
Dixon goes rebound,
goes right.

10:04.420 --> 10:06.290
2 points,
and the crowd goes wild!

10:06.290 --> 10:07.460
[ Imitates crowd ]
Kevin: Hey, Jon.

10:07.460 --> 10:08.620
Hey, Kev.

10:08.620 --> 10:09.790
Oh, none for me today.
I'm driving.

10:09.790 --> 10:11.120
Yeah, okay. [ Laughs ]

10:11.120 --> 10:12.960
-What's new?
-Ah, not much, you know.

10:12.960 --> 10:15.290
Oh, come on, Kev.

10:15.290 --> 10:17.000
You know I won't be able
to pass out,

10:17.000 --> 10:18.290
which means
I'll be sitting here

10:18.290 --> 10:19.960
for the better part
of three hours

10:19.960 --> 10:21.460
staring
at a blank wall.

10:21.460 --> 10:23.290
How 'bout you embellish this
just a teeny bit?

10:23.290 --> 10:24.960
You know what?
How about...

10:24.960 --> 10:26.960
No. Kev.
...we just listen...

10:26.960 --> 10:28.830
-Oh, yeah. Give it to me.
-...to some music.

10:28.830 --> 10:31.170
No, no, no.

10:31.170 --> 10:33.830
[ Macklemore's "Can't Hold Us"
plays on radio ]
Oh, not this song again.

10:33.830 --> 10:34.790
Kevin: Yep.
If I die,

10:34.790 --> 10:35.790
I'm leaving you
all my music.

10:35.790 --> 10:38.170
There you go.
I know what this is.

10:38.170 --> 10:40.120
I have died.
This is Hell.

10:40.120 --> 10:41.330
Excuse me, Gary.

10:41.330 --> 10:42.790
Trying to stay positive
over here.

10:42.790 --> 10:44.120
Are you, Linda?

10:44.120 --> 10:45.960
Because everything
you're doing

10:45.960 --> 10:47.670
seems super negative
to me.

10:47.670 --> 10:49.500
Okay, okay, okay. Come on.
Kev, sing it with me.

10:49.500 --> 10:51.500
Here we go.
Both: ♪ Can we go back? ♪

10:51.500 --> 10:53.000
♪ This is the moment ♪

10:53.000 --> 10:54.380
♪ Tonight is the night ♪

10:54.380 --> 10:56.000
♪ We'll fight till it's over ♪

10:56.000 --> 10:57.540
♪ So we put our hands up ♪

10:57.540 --> 10:59.170
♪ Like the ceiling
can't hold us ♪

10:59.170 --> 11:01.000
What is that?
Why are you doing that?

11:01.000 --> 11:04.710
♪ Like the ceiling
can't hold us ♪

11:04.710 --> 11:06.040
♪ This is the moment ♪

11:06.040 --> 11:07.540
♪ Tonight is the night ♪

11:07.540 --> 11:09.330
♪ We'll fight
till it's over ♪

11:09.330 --> 11:10.710
[ Vomits ]

11:10.710 --> 11:12.000
Okay, okay.
It's all right.

11:12.000 --> 11:13.540
It's all right,
it's all right.

11:13.540 --> 11:14.880
[ Groans ]

11:14.880 --> 11:19.170
♪♪

11:19.170 --> 11:21.710
[ Pants ]

11:21.710 --> 11:23.880
No.

11:23.880 --> 11:25.170
You're gonna beat this.

11:25.170 --> 11:32.380
♪♪

11:32.380 --> 11:33.880
Gary: [ Sighs ]

11:33.880 --> 11:35.210
Maggie: What are you
talking about?

11:35.210 --> 11:39.380
Hall and Oates is clearly
the best duo of all time.

11:39.380 --> 11:43.080
Says anyone who's never listened
to Simon & Garfunkel.

11:43.080 --> 11:45.040
I --
"Bridge over
Troubled Water,"

11:45.040 --> 11:46.420
"50 Ways
to Leave Your Lover"...

11:46.420 --> 11:49.040
Both of which were written
by Simon, not Garfunkel,

11:49.040 --> 11:50.380
so you lose.

11:50.380 --> 11:51.380
[ Laughs ]

11:51.380 --> 11:53.250
"Sound of Silence,"
"Old Friends"?

11:53.250 --> 11:54.380
Andrew: I think even Oates
would admit

11:54.380 --> 11:56.710
that Simon & Garfunkel
are better.

11:56.710 --> 11:58.380
Sorry, I didn't mean
to eavesdrop.

11:58.380 --> 12:00.420
I'm -- I'm just
a huge Simon & Garfunkel fan.

12:00.420 --> 12:01.710
[ Laughs ]

12:01.710 --> 12:02.880
Really?
Yeah.

12:02.880 --> 12:04.250
[ Keypad beeping ]

12:04.250 --> 12:05.750
If you had to pick
just one song,

12:05.750 --> 12:07.250
what would it be?

12:07.250 --> 12:09.580
Uh..."Maneater,"
no question about it.

12:09.580 --> 12:12.420
[ Both laugh ]

12:12.420 --> 12:14.920
Hey, um, I don't know
what you're doing later,

12:14.920 --> 12:18.250
but I own this, uh,
old-school bar downtown.

12:18.250 --> 12:20.420
It's called
Blind Dog Whiskey,

12:20.420 --> 12:22.420
and I think you'd love
what's on the jukebox.

12:22.420 --> 12:24.580
And if you come down,
the first round will be on me.

12:24.580 --> 12:26.420
Oh.

12:26.420 --> 12:28.080
I, um...

12:28.080 --> 12:29.750
Oh, whoops. Sorry.

12:31.250 --> 12:32.960
I didn't -- I didn't realize
you were already part of a duo.

12:35.290 --> 12:37.420
Yeah.

12:37.420 --> 12:38.580
Well, I don't know
who your Garfunkel is,

12:38.580 --> 12:39.790
but he's a lucky guy.

12:46.420 --> 12:47.920
Wow.

12:47.920 --> 12:50.290
[ Doorbell rings ]

12:50.290 --> 12:52.290
What's up, Dad?
What are you doing here?

12:52.290 --> 12:53.290
My daughter-in-law
called me.

12:55.460 --> 12:56.830
Regina: Hey.

12:56.830 --> 12:58.120
-Mwah.
-Mwah.

12:58.120 --> 12:59.620
How's it going, beautiful?
Great, gorgeous.

12:59.620 --> 13:03.290
So, where's the sink
that needs fixing?

13:03.290 --> 13:04.330
You called my dad?

13:04.330 --> 13:05.620
I thought
you were gonna call the super.

13:05.620 --> 13:07.790
Well, it's less weird
when I hug your dad.

13:07.790 --> 13:09.460
All right, I'm leaving.

13:09.460 --> 13:11.290
Feel free to talk about
how great I am when I'm gone.

13:11.290 --> 13:12.790
[ Laughs ]

13:12.790 --> 13:14.830
I love you.
Love you. Have fun.

13:14.830 --> 13:17.120
Okay, uh...

13:17.120 --> 13:18.670
It's the sink
in the master bathroom,

13:18.670 --> 13:20.290
and I'll be out here
if you need anything.

13:20.290 --> 13:22.290
Oh, I'm not here
to fix the sink, son.

13:22.290 --> 13:24.620
I'm here to help you
fix the sink.

13:24.620 --> 13:25.960
Don't dawdle.

13:29.790 --> 13:36.380
♪♪

13:36.380 --> 13:38.170
Delilah: I don't know.

13:38.170 --> 13:41.170
Part of me wonders
if I should take the ring off.

13:41.170 --> 13:43.330
Uh-huh.
And not because
of that guy.

13:43.330 --> 13:45.170
[ Chuckles ]
Stop.

13:45.170 --> 13:49.670
Just because of everything
that's happened.

13:49.670 --> 13:51.000
If I keep it on,

13:51.000 --> 13:54.040
I feel like
I'm making the statement

13:54.040 --> 13:56.000
that my marriage
was perfect.

13:59.000 --> 14:01.000
And yet,
if I take it off,

14:01.000 --> 14:03.500
I feel like
it's just another example

14:03.500 --> 14:06.380
of me not being faithful
to Jon.

14:06.380 --> 14:09.830
So...

14:09.830 --> 14:13.670
So we're not meeting Pump 6
for a drink.

14:13.670 --> 14:16.040
[ Chuckles ]

14:18.920 --> 14:20.710
The hell is that?

14:20.710 --> 14:21.880
You told me to get
my tools.

14:21.880 --> 14:23.540
How do you not have
a proper tool box?

14:23.540 --> 14:25.920
You're a grown man
and a homeowner.

14:25.920 --> 14:27.710
And yet, somehow,
I made it to today.

14:27.710 --> 14:29.210
Day isn't over yet.

14:29.210 --> 14:31.380
Get down here.

14:31.380 --> 14:33.040
I'm not getting dirtier
than you.

14:36.920 --> 14:40.420
Okay.
First things first.

14:40.420 --> 14:43.540
Remove
the old drain assembly.

14:43.540 --> 14:44.710
Is this the point
where I tell you

14:44.710 --> 14:46.710
that I don't know
what the drain assembly is?

14:46.710 --> 14:48.420
It's right there
by your hand.

14:48.420 --> 14:49.250
Oh.

14:51.380 --> 14:54.210
Good.

14:54.210 --> 14:57.460
Mom told me
you quit the commercials.

14:57.460 --> 14:59.580
You win the lottery
and not tell your father?

14:59.580 --> 15:00.580
I'm writing.

15:00.580 --> 15:03.120
Directing commercials
didn't make me happy.

15:03.120 --> 15:05.960
It's a job. It's not supposed
to make you happy.

15:05.960 --> 15:07.460
Loosen that
while I get the snake.

15:07.460 --> 15:08.620
Oh!

15:08.620 --> 15:10.960
[ Sputters ]

15:10.960 --> 15:12.920
Oh!

15:12.920 --> 15:14.120
We should've had
a bucket.

15:14.120 --> 15:16.460
And now
you'll never forget.

15:16.460 --> 15:19.420
I'll get the snake.
[ Laughs ]

15:19.420 --> 15:20.750
[ Sighs ]

15:20.750 --> 15:22.080
[ Knocking on door ]

15:22.080 --> 15:23.920
Hello?

15:23.920 --> 15:25.080
Dad!

15:25.080 --> 15:27.120
-Buddy!
-Hi.

15:27.120 --> 15:28.250
-Hey.
-Hey.

15:28.250 --> 15:29.290
Who is this?

15:29.290 --> 15:30.750
This is my new friend,
Jack.

15:30.750 --> 15:32.580
Jack. What's happening?

15:32.580 --> 15:33.750
Hey, where's Mom?

15:33.750 --> 15:35.080
Uh, she had
to go to work.

15:35.080 --> 15:37.080
Oh.
Well, is Grandma here?

15:37.080 --> 15:38.620
Hunter: All right, boys.
Here we go.

15:38.620 --> 15:41.120
Two orders of TIE fighter-shaped
grilled cheese.

15:41.120 --> 15:42.170
Hey, Eddie.
Thank you.

15:42.170 --> 15:43.790
Hey.
Hunter.

15:43.790 --> 15:45.460
Yeah.
I remember.

15:45.460 --> 15:48.670
Yeah, Katie just wanted me
to cover until her mom got here.

15:48.670 --> 15:51.170
Can I interest you in a TIE
fighter-shaped grilled cheese?

15:51.170 --> 15:52.170
No, thanks.

15:52.170 --> 15:54.830
♪♪

16:00.670 --> 16:01.790
[ Macklemore's "Can't Hold Us"
plays on radio ]
Gary: No!

16:01.790 --> 16:03.120
Hey, hey.
Kevin.

16:03.120 --> 16:05.460
-This you?
-You're killing me.

16:05.460 --> 16:06.330
This is what's going
to kill me.

16:06.330 --> 16:07.670
♪ Yeah ♪

16:07.670 --> 16:09.000
♪ Let's go! ♪

16:09.000 --> 16:10.620
No, let -- let's not go.
Let's stop.

16:10.620 --> 16:11.620
All right.

16:11.620 --> 16:13.000
♪ All right, okay ♪

16:13.000 --> 16:14.830
♪ Unh, all right, okay ♪

16:14.830 --> 16:16.460
♪ All right, okay ♪

16:16.460 --> 16:18.500
It's not all right.
It's not -- It's not okay.

16:18.500 --> 16:20.330
[ Rapping ]
♪ Return of the Mack,
get 'em, what it is ♪

16:20.330 --> 16:21.830
♪ What it does, what it is,
what it isn't ♪

16:21.830 --> 16:23.170
♪ Looking for a better way
to get up out of bed ♪

16:23.170 --> 16:24.330
♪ Instead of getting
on the Internet ♪
[ Laughs ]

16:24.330 --> 16:25.210
♪ And checking a new hit me,
get up ♪

16:25.210 --> 16:26.670
♪ Thrift shop,
pimp-strut walkin' ♪

16:26.670 --> 16:28.500
♪ Little bit of humble,
little bit of cautious ♪

16:28.500 --> 16:29.830
♪ Somewhere between
like Rocky and Cosby ♪
You're an idiot.

16:29.830 --> 16:31.000
♪ Sweater game,
nope, nope ♪

16:31.000 --> 16:34.000
Oh!
And the crowd goes wild.

16:34.000 --> 16:35.670
Kevin: [ Laughs ]

16:35.670 --> 16:37.170
Ah, ah, ah, ah.

16:37.170 --> 16:39.330
Linda. Careful.

16:39.330 --> 16:40.500
You almost smiled.

16:40.500 --> 16:42.170
[ Scraping ]

16:42.170 --> 16:43.830
Boom.

16:43.830 --> 16:45.210
How's that for a view?

16:45.210 --> 16:46.670
It's the Cambridge side
of the Charles,

16:46.670 --> 16:48.330
so you can pretend you went
to Harvard with me.

16:48.330 --> 16:49.670
Oh, Kev,
did you hear that?

16:49.670 --> 16:51.170
Jon went to Harvard.

16:51.170 --> 16:52.330
Oh, really?

16:52.330 --> 16:53.830
He'd like you to know
that he went to Harvard.

16:53.830 --> 16:55.170
It's Har-- Harvard.

16:55.170 --> 16:56.380
Okay, two things.

16:56.380 --> 16:59.670
One, you're not staring
at a blank wall anymore.

16:59.670 --> 17:02.380
And two,
you're gonna beat this.

17:02.380 --> 17:04.210
Mm.
You are.

17:04.210 --> 17:05.710
Just watch.
You're gonna outlive me.

17:05.710 --> 17:07.710
You're gonna be here long after
I'm gone telling people --

17:07.710 --> 17:09.380
You went to Harvard.

17:09.380 --> 17:11.040
People need to know.

17:15.210 --> 17:17.750
So get better, okay?

17:17.750 --> 17:20.210
As soon as you do, we're gonna
rent one of those boats,

17:20.210 --> 17:22.250
and we're gonna go out
on that water.

17:22.250 --> 17:25.040
The only thing that's gonna
make you vomit is seasickness

17:25.040 --> 17:27.040
or one too many mimosas.

17:30.540 --> 17:36.040
♪♪

17:36.040 --> 17:41.750
♪♪

17:41.750 --> 17:43.920
Donny, if you pull the trigger
now, you get nothing.

17:43.920 --> 17:45.120
Donny: How do I know
that I'm gonna get something?

17:45.120 --> 17:46.580
No, I told you,
the subway vote is back on.

17:46.580 --> 17:47.920
I can't wait for that,
Ashley.

17:47.920 --> 17:49.250
Oh, really?
After all the business

17:49.250 --> 17:50.250
that Jon has thrown
your way,

17:50.250 --> 17:51.420
you're just gonna, what,

17:51.420 --> 17:53.960
sit there
and screw his family over?

17:53.960 --> 17:55.080
Just let me --
Let me see what I can do.

17:55.080 --> 17:56.250
Yeah, "see what you can do."

17:56.250 --> 17:58.120
[ Cellphone beeps ]

18:00.420 --> 18:01.580
Hey.

18:01.580 --> 18:03.250
Hey.

18:03.250 --> 18:04.750
You wanna get a drink?

18:04.750 --> 18:07.080
Yeah. Yeah, I do.

18:07.080 --> 18:09.420
[ Indistinct conversations ]

18:09.420 --> 18:11.250
Hey.

18:11.250 --> 18:13.120
Eddie.
Uh, what are you doing here?

18:13.120 --> 18:15.920
Uh, the question is,
what are you doing here?

18:15.920 --> 18:17.420
You're supposed to be
watching our son.

18:17.420 --> 18:19.580
Instead, I find him at home
with your new boyfriend?

18:21.750 --> 18:23.750
[ Scoffs, sighs ]

18:28.290 --> 18:31.170
First of all,
Hunter's not my boyfriend.

18:31.170 --> 18:32.460
He is a colleague

18:32.460 --> 18:34.830
who is graciously
helping me out.

18:34.830 --> 18:39.000
Second, this is my time
with Theo.

18:39.000 --> 18:41.620
Well...I think the point is

18:41.620 --> 18:43.620
that we need
to communicate better.

18:43.620 --> 18:46.290
Like how I found out from Regina
that Delilah's pregnant?

18:48.790 --> 18:49.960
[ Sighs ]

18:49.960 --> 18:52.170
Look,
I know the baby's Jon's.

18:54.460 --> 18:57.330
I would have liked
to have heard that from you.

18:57.330 --> 18:58.960
You're right,

18:58.960 --> 19:00.500
and I'm sorry.

19:02.790 --> 19:04.620
But Theo needs us,
especially now,

19:04.620 --> 19:07.210
and when he can't be
with you,

19:07.210 --> 19:09.000
I would like for him
to be with me.

19:11.880 --> 19:13.040
What?

19:16.170 --> 19:18.170
All I want
is to be with him.

19:21.380 --> 19:22.830
Hey.
I got to get
back to work.

19:22.830 --> 19:24.500
♪♪

19:24.500 --> 19:26.500
[ Sighs ]

19:26.500 --> 19:28.710
Grief is complicated,

19:28.710 --> 19:33.000
and it's often exacerbated
by external factors.

19:33.000 --> 19:35.670
Every state,
with the exception of Utah,

19:35.670 --> 19:37.710
is, um...

19:43.500 --> 19:45.670
You know, th--

19:45.670 --> 19:50.210
this is not about,
um...a study.

19:50.210 --> 19:52.040
Um...

19:59.710 --> 20:01.880
[ Sighs ] When I was 22,

20:01.880 --> 20:06.380
I lost my best friend --

20:06.380 --> 20:08.040
my brother.

20:08.920 --> 20:11.880
He was your age.

20:11.880 --> 20:14.710
Any one of you
could have been his friend,

20:14.710 --> 20:16.420
could have been the one

20:16.420 --> 20:20.250
to stop him from drinking
and getting in that car,

20:20.250 --> 20:21.380
but you didn't.

20:23.880 --> 20:26.210
And neither did I.

20:28.540 --> 20:29.920
I'm ashamed to admit this,

20:29.920 --> 20:35.580
but when I first got that call,

20:35.580 --> 20:38.960
I felt relief.

20:38.960 --> 20:42.250
I didn't have
to keep checking my phone,

20:42.250 --> 20:43.790
wondering if it was gonna be
the hospital

20:43.790 --> 20:46.790
saying that he hurt someone
or himself,

20:46.790 --> 20:53.250
and that relief...

20:53.250 --> 20:55.620
uh, just makes me feel worse.

20:59.920 --> 21:02.620
I have so many feelings
that I haven't processed

21:02.620 --> 21:05.750
because I am...

21:05.750 --> 21:07.580
[ Sighs ]

21:07.580 --> 21:10.420
...too ashamed to admit
that I have them.

21:12.080 --> 21:14.790
And that is
complicated bereavement.

21:15.790 --> 21:17.330
[ Knock on door ]

21:17.330 --> 21:18.620
Uh-huh.

21:18.620 --> 21:20.460
Partner blazer.

21:20.460 --> 21:22.460
Oh, that's right.
The big interview is today.

21:22.460 --> 21:24.120
So, when they put your name
on the door,

21:24.120 --> 21:25.460
you still gonna talk
to me?

21:25.460 --> 21:28.120
[ Sighs ]

21:28.120 --> 21:31.290
Okay, what happened?
Where'd you go?

21:31.290 --> 21:35.120
[ Sighing ]
Uh, I don't know.

21:35.120 --> 21:37.120
Every day since law school,

21:37.120 --> 21:39.960
I've been working so hard
to make partner,

21:39.960 --> 21:43.460
and now it's
on my doorstep.

21:43.460 --> 21:44.790
How do I take it,

21:44.790 --> 21:47.460
knowing it'll pull me away
from Theo even more?

21:49.830 --> 21:50.620
You know what I would do?

21:52.120 --> 21:54.040
Trust your gut.

21:54.040 --> 21:55.830
It continues to amaze me.

21:57.000 --> 21:59.000
[ Sighs ]

21:59.000 --> 22:00.500
That settles it.

22:00.500 --> 22:03.000
If I make partner,
I'll still talk to you.

22:06.710 --> 22:07.830
Gary:
All right, let's do this.

22:07.830 --> 22:09.330
We're gonna party!

22:09.330 --> 22:11.330
Cancer-free, one year,
people.

22:11.330 --> 22:12.500
[ Applause ]
Thank you very much.

22:12.500 --> 22:14.000
Sorry if that's
too much information,

22:14.000 --> 22:16.000
but it's true.

22:16.000 --> 22:17.670
Seriously, let's get crazy.

22:17.670 --> 22:20.000
Oh, what exactly is crazy?

22:20.000 --> 22:21.670
Dancing on the bar?
[ Smacks bar ]

22:21.670 --> 22:23.210
Mm,
not with those heels,

22:23.210 --> 22:25.000
and not with this body.

22:25.000 --> 22:26.330
What else do we got?

22:26.330 --> 22:28.670
Shots?
Are shots still a thing?

22:28.670 --> 22:30.170
Can we get two shots
of tequila?

22:30.170 --> 22:31.000
Something nice?

22:31.000 --> 22:34.000
Oh, in fact,
shots for everybody.

22:34.000 --> 22:36.880
[ Cheers and applause ]

22:36.880 --> 22:38.540
Wow, my voice
really carries.

22:38.540 --> 22:41.540
Maybe, um, take it down a shelf
for the rest of the group?

22:41.540 --> 22:42.880
Thanks, man.

22:42.880 --> 22:45.040
And...

22:45.040 --> 22:46.420
To?
Remission.

22:46.420 --> 22:48.040
[ Glasses clink ]
Living.

22:48.040 --> 22:51.880
[ Indistinct conversations ]

22:51.880 --> 22:53.920
You know...
Mm.

22:53.920 --> 22:56.040
When I was going through
chemo,

22:56.040 --> 22:58.080
I was pretty convinced
I was gonna die.

22:59.750 --> 23:03.210
But Jon was
so determined.

23:03.210 --> 23:04.710
Never seen him fight harder
to close a deal.

23:04.710 --> 23:06.210
[ Chuckles ]

23:06.210 --> 23:08.080
Told me I was gonna
outlive him,

23:08.080 --> 23:10.380
like he knew this
for a fact,

23:10.380 --> 23:12.040
that I would be around
long after he was gone

23:12.040 --> 23:14.210
reminding people
that he --

23:14.210 --> 23:19.080
♪♪

23:19.080 --> 23:20.580
Oh, my God.

23:20.580 --> 23:22.250
♪♪

23:22.250 --> 23:24.080
Gary.
Oh, my God.

23:24.080 --> 23:26.120
Do you think
he was telling me?

23:26.120 --> 23:28.080
♪♪

23:33.620 --> 23:35.920
There's no way Jon was planning
it for that long.

23:35.920 --> 23:39.080
That was a year ago.
That's crazy.

23:39.080 --> 23:41.750
Right?

23:41.750 --> 23:43.420
Was he trying to tell me?

23:43.420 --> 23:45.420
I ask myself the same thing
every day.

23:46.920 --> 23:50.580
What did we miss, Ashley?
What didn't we see?

23:50.580 --> 23:52.290
Is there a side to Jon
that we didn't know,

23:52.290 --> 23:54.460
or at least
that I didn't know?

23:54.460 --> 23:56.580
I mean, you were on every call.
You saw everything.

23:56.580 --> 23:58.920
Hell, you knew my chemo schedule
better than I did.

24:00.960 --> 24:03.170
Was there anything,
any sign?

24:06.170 --> 24:08.790
Was he having
financial troubles?

24:08.790 --> 24:10.290
Do -- Do you think --

24:10.290 --> 24:11.960
think he was having
an affair?

24:11.960 --> 24:18.290
♪♪

24:18.290 --> 24:19.790
I wasn't gonna say anything,
and -- and look,

24:19.790 --> 24:22.790
maybe this isn't anything
to begin with.

24:22.790 --> 24:25.460
But did Jon ever mention
a Barbara Morgan?

24:25.460 --> 24:26.960
No.

24:28.290 --> 24:29.290
No.

24:29.290 --> 24:30.500
Outside of Delilah,

24:30.500 --> 24:33.120
you're the only woman
in his life.

24:33.120 --> 24:34.960
Who is Barbara Morgan?

24:37.000 --> 24:38.620
I don't know.

24:38.620 --> 24:39.830
Really.

24:39.830 --> 24:43.500
He -- He just kicked me off
a call one time,

24:43.500 --> 24:45.500
and he's only done that
a handful of times.

24:45.500 --> 24:46.540
I'm sure it's nothing.

24:46.540 --> 24:49.330
I -- Just --
I'm looking for answers, too.

24:49.330 --> 24:51.210
Okay.

24:51.210 --> 24:53.540
Just take a break,
all right,

24:53.540 --> 24:57.710
'cause the Bruins are gonna
take the ice in 15 minutes.

24:57.710 --> 24:59.710
The guys bailed on me.

24:59.710 --> 25:02.380
Would you like to go
to the game?

25:02.380 --> 25:04.330
I saw your key chain.

25:04.330 --> 25:05.670
I didn't realize
you were a fan.

25:05.670 --> 25:07.500
♪♪

25:07.500 --> 25:08.330
Yeah.

25:08.330 --> 25:10.170
Yeah, sure.
[ Chuckles ]

25:10.170 --> 25:12.830
[ Cellphone buzzes ]
Great.

25:12.830 --> 25:14.170
Take your call.

25:14.170 --> 25:15.330
I'm gonna take a leak.

25:15.330 --> 25:16.830
Unless you think
that's gross,

25:16.830 --> 25:18.830
in which case,
just pretend I didn't say it.

25:18.830 --> 25:20.670
Say what?

25:22.540 --> 25:24.210
Hello?

25:26.710 --> 25:28.710
Yeah, I'm with him.

25:32.380 --> 25:34.250
Love it.

25:34.250 --> 25:36.710
Man, I ate a banana.
I'm full of potassium.

25:36.710 --> 25:38.580
What's next
on the lesson plan, Pop?

25:38.580 --> 25:47.380
♪♪

25:47.380 --> 25:48.710
What are these?

25:48.710 --> 25:51.710
♪♪

25:51.710 --> 25:54.880
Dad...

25:54.880 --> 25:56.250
I tried, man.

25:56.250 --> 26:00.750
I -- I tried to be the man
you taught me to be.

26:00.750 --> 26:03.040
I tried
not to ask for help...

26:03.040 --> 26:04.750
Help for what?

26:06.460 --> 26:13.080
Sometimes I get really sad
for no reason.

26:13.080 --> 26:14.750
Actually,
a lot of times.

26:16.960 --> 26:20.420
I have clinical depression.

26:20.420 --> 26:23.250
I've had it
for a while.

26:23.250 --> 26:25.250
I know that you -- you --

26:25.250 --> 26:26.920
you want to teach me
how to fix the sink,

26:26.920 --> 26:29.580
but me taking those pills,

26:29.580 --> 26:32.080
quitting my job,

26:32.080 --> 26:34.580
that's me
trying to fix me.

26:34.580 --> 26:38.080
♪♪

26:38.080 --> 26:39.960
Do they help?

26:39.960 --> 26:41.620
Y-- My doctor says
it's a process,

26:41.620 --> 26:44.460
but they --
t-they seem to be.

26:44.460 --> 26:48.290
So you're seeing
a shrink?

26:48.290 --> 26:51.960
Yes.

26:51.960 --> 26:53.960
It's something
I need to do.

26:53.960 --> 27:02.500
♪♪

27:02.500 --> 27:11.290
♪♪

27:11.290 --> 27:12.960
Nice job
with the sink.

27:21.290 --> 27:23.960
I had no idea
about your brother.

27:26.170 --> 27:28.000
Is he the reason
why you don't drive?

27:35.000 --> 27:37.210
You know, it's taken me
almost six years

27:37.210 --> 27:41.830
to even be able to say
that stuff out loud.

27:41.830 --> 27:43.500
There are things
I don't think

27:43.500 --> 27:45.830
I'll ever be able
to say out loud.

27:49.210 --> 27:50.830
When I first met you,

27:50.830 --> 27:53.330
you said what you needed
was a time machine.

27:53.330 --> 27:55.000
[ Chuckles ]

27:55.000 --> 27:56.830
Where would you go
if you had one?

28:00.210 --> 28:04.670
I -- I'd go back
two years ago.

28:04.670 --> 28:06.830
That's --

28:06.830 --> 28:09.920
That's when I lost him,

28:09.920 --> 28:12.040
when he became distant

28:12.040 --> 28:14.540
and buried himself in work.

28:17.540 --> 28:19.040
He shut me out.

28:23.080 --> 28:25.040
Everybody thinks
that I cheated on Jon,

28:25.040 --> 28:27.540
but...

28:27.540 --> 28:29.380
He left me.

28:29.380 --> 28:31.580
He left me two years ago
for reasons I just --

28:31.580 --> 28:34.540
I still don't understand.

28:34.540 --> 28:37.040
And then he just --

28:37.040 --> 28:39.210
He left me again
seven weeks ago,

28:39.210 --> 28:43.210
not for someone,
just for nothing.

28:45.710 --> 28:47.420
When you asked me
why I wasn't ready

28:47.420 --> 28:49.710
to take my ring off
earlier --

28:49.710 --> 28:52.750
'cause I should have either
taken it off two years ago

28:52.750 --> 28:55.580
or fought for him.

28:55.580 --> 29:01.420
♪♪

29:01.420 --> 29:03.920
Henry: And so, Katherine,
I'll make this quick.

29:03.920 --> 29:05.460
We couldn't be more thrilled
to welcome you

29:05.460 --> 29:07.580
as the newest partner
at Newman, Duffy, and Han.

29:07.580 --> 29:10.080
-Congratulations.
-That is amazing.

29:10.080 --> 29:12.920
I've wanted this
for so long.

29:12.920 --> 29:14.750
I would be thrilled
to accept.

29:14.750 --> 29:17.920
Great.

29:17.920 --> 29:20.750
I just have one request.

29:20.750 --> 29:24.960
I know it's unusual,
but it's non-negotiable.

29:24.960 --> 29:26.920
Every night,
from 6:00 to 8:00,

29:26.920 --> 29:28.750
I need to be off the grid.

29:28.750 --> 29:30.580
I'll work long into the night,
every day,

29:30.580 --> 29:33.120
like I have
for the past nine years.

29:33.120 --> 29:35.170
But I need to be home for dinner
with my son every night.

29:37.120 --> 29:39.620
Well...

29:39.620 --> 29:42.620
We'll need to discuss it
with the partner committee.

29:42.620 --> 29:43.960
Of course.

29:45.000 --> 29:46.290
Thank you.

29:46.290 --> 29:47.960
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

29:47.960 --> 29:51.830
♪♪

29:51.830 --> 29:53.290
[ Door closes ]

29:53.290 --> 29:57.960
♪♪

29:57.960 --> 29:59.500
[ Car door opens ]

29:59.500 --> 30:01.000
Gary: Now Rask's not gonna be
in goal tonight.

30:01.000 --> 30:02.460
-Thank you.
-That's fantastic.

30:02.460 --> 30:04.120
You know,
it doesn't matter.

30:04.120 --> 30:06.290
Doesn't matter.
We're still gonna win.

30:06.290 --> 30:08.120
You got to support your B's,
am I right?

30:09.790 --> 30:11.120
Why are we at my place?

30:11.120 --> 30:12.960
I just need to make
one quick stop.

30:14.500 --> 30:16.500
Oh, Ash, I...

30:16.500 --> 30:17.710
I'm sorry.
You know what?

30:17.710 --> 30:19.670
I think I've misled you
about what this is and --

30:19.670 --> 30:21.500
Oh. Oh, Gary, no.

30:21.500 --> 30:24.170
[ Laughs ] I think
I may have misled you.

30:25.330 --> 30:28.000
All: Surprise!

30:28.000 --> 30:30.040
Eddie: All right!
One year cancer-free!

30:30.040 --> 30:32.330
Whoo!

30:32.330 --> 30:34.330
Delilah:
Take that, cancer!

30:34.330 --> 30:35.670
[ Laughs ]

30:35.670 --> 30:38.040
-Happy remission!
-All right!

30:42.210 --> 30:43.330
-One year cancer-free!
-Happy remission!

30:43.330 --> 30:44.040
[ Scoffs ]
Okay, wait -- wait a minute.

30:44.040 --> 30:45.500
Just wait a minute.

30:45.500 --> 30:46.710
You -- You said you had
a guitar lesson.

30:46.710 --> 30:48.040
Yes. "Pinball Wizard."

30:48.040 --> 30:49.380
That is this lesson.

30:49.380 --> 30:51.000
And all this time,
you've been saying

30:51.000 --> 30:52.710
you had to go
to Dave Matthews?

30:52.710 --> 30:54.210
Let's be clear.

30:54.210 --> 30:56.540
I am never going to see
Dave Matthews.

30:56.540 --> 31:00.040
[ Laughter ]

31:00.040 --> 31:02.540
Wow.
This -- This is amazing.

31:02.540 --> 31:04.210
What's amazing is getting us
all together

31:04.210 --> 31:06.380
to finally celebrate
something happy.

31:06.380 --> 31:08.210
You didn't have
to do all this.

31:08.210 --> 31:10.040
That's what makes it
such a sweet gesture.

31:10.040 --> 31:12.040
♪♪

31:12.040 --> 31:13.540
Congratulations.

31:13.540 --> 31:14.880
Eddie: Right?

31:14.880 --> 31:17.210
By the way, Rome,
I love Dave Matthews.

31:17.210 --> 31:18.750
Dave Matthews
is actually talented.

31:18.750 --> 31:19.880
Rome: I hate knowing
Dave Matthews.

31:19.880 --> 31:21.580
Speech. Speech!

31:21.580 --> 31:23.540
Speech! What?

31:23.540 --> 31:24.920
[ Applause ]

31:24.920 --> 31:26.880
[ Clinking glasses ]

31:26.880 --> 31:28.710
[ Sighs ]

31:28.710 --> 31:31.380
Uh...I just, uh...

31:33.710 --> 31:35.580
Excuse me.

31:35.580 --> 31:41.920
♪♪

31:41.920 --> 31:48.290
♪♪

31:48.290 --> 31:51.420
[ Sighs ]

31:51.420 --> 31:55.080
Not exactly sure what's going on
in that head of yours.

31:56.920 --> 32:03.920
But I just wanted to say
that I love you,

32:03.920 --> 32:06.960
and I'm happy
you're still on this planet.

32:08.250 --> 32:09.790
Thanks, D.

32:12.620 --> 32:14.620
But he should be here, too.

32:18.080 --> 32:19.960
Yeah.

32:22.460 --> 32:23.620
Word on the street is

32:23.620 --> 32:26.330
you've been storming
out of rooms a lot today.

32:26.330 --> 32:27.830
What? No.

32:27.830 --> 32:30.290
I'm just trying
to get my 10,000 steps.

32:30.290 --> 32:33.960
[ Chuckles ]

32:33.960 --> 32:36.790
You're allowed
to be angry.

32:36.790 --> 32:39.170
You're allowed to feel
whatever --

32:39.170 --> 32:41.170
whatever it is
that you feel.

32:44.960 --> 32:48.290
So, this is the widow
helping the friend grieve?

32:48.290 --> 32:50.120
[ Scoffs ]

32:50.120 --> 32:52.330
It's not my best moment.

32:52.330 --> 32:54.620
All I'm saying is,

32:54.620 --> 32:56.670
we all have different ways
of coping.

32:56.670 --> 33:04.710
♪♪

33:04.710 --> 33:06.670
Here's mine.

33:07.500 --> 33:09.000
Oh, God.

33:10.500 --> 33:12.210
[ Clears throat ]
Okay, you guys want a speech?

33:12.210 --> 33:13.500
Here we go. Here's a speech.

33:13.500 --> 33:15.330
Thank you all very much
for this party.

33:15.330 --> 33:16.500
It's amazing.

33:16.500 --> 33:18.000
Probably doesn't seem like
I mean that,

33:18.000 --> 33:19.830
but I do, truly.

33:19.830 --> 33:24.210
I just -- Apparently,
I'm angry right now, right?

33:24.210 --> 33:25.500
Shocker.

33:25.500 --> 33:27.040
And I am.

33:27.040 --> 33:28.710
I'm -- I'm --
I'm unbelievably angry,

33:28.710 --> 33:29.710
but not at you.

33:29.710 --> 33:31.170
You guys have all been amazing.

33:31.170 --> 33:33.170
I mean, should we have scalped
the Bruins tickets?

33:33.170 --> 33:34.670
Probably. You get it.

33:34.670 --> 33:36.330
[ Clears throat ]

33:36.330 --> 33:38.170
Katherine, you took off work.
That never happens.

33:38.170 --> 33:39.670
Thank you.

33:39.670 --> 33:41.330
This is all...

33:41.330 --> 33:43.380
[ Sighs ]

33:43.380 --> 33:44.750
...so sweet.

33:44.750 --> 33:48.210
But I'm so angry at the person
who is not here.

33:48.210 --> 33:51.210
I am so angry at Jon.

33:53.710 --> 33:57.040
And you -- yeah, you --

33:57.040 --> 33:59.380
you gave the eulogy,
and that was crazy,

33:59.380 --> 34:03.250
because everybody knows
that I'm funnier.

34:03.250 --> 34:07.380
But...it was beautiful,

34:07.380 --> 34:09.880
and you knocked it
out of the park.

34:09.880 --> 34:12.250
And I'm glad it was you
because, you know --

34:12.250 --> 34:14.210
you know what would have
happened if it was me?

34:16.580 --> 34:17.580
I would've done this.

34:17.580 --> 34:18.420
Eddie: Gary, no!

34:20.540 --> 34:23.040
I would've done that!

34:23.040 --> 34:24.380
And I would've talked about

34:24.380 --> 34:27.420
how Jon fought so hard
to help me live

34:27.420 --> 34:29.580
and how he came
to the treatment center so often

34:29.580 --> 34:32.460
that the other patients thought
that he had cancer, too.

34:34.580 --> 34:37.250
You, Jon, you --

34:37.250 --> 34:38.420
you went through the whole thing
with me,

34:38.420 --> 34:39.750
and you convinced me --

34:39.750 --> 34:41.750
you convinced me to live,

34:41.750 --> 34:43.580
and then you left me.

34:49.080 --> 34:50.750
[ Voice breaking ]
We were supposed to go on
these little boats together.

34:50.750 --> 34:52.290
That's so stupid.

34:55.080 --> 34:57.420
[ Sobbing ]

34:57.420 --> 35:00.620
♪♪

35:00.620 --> 35:02.250
We made plans,

35:02.250 --> 35:04.080
and I thought
they were the same plans,

35:04.080 --> 35:07.620
and apparently they were not.

35:07.620 --> 35:08.460
[ Sighs ]

35:08.460 --> 35:15.000
♪♪

35:15.000 --> 35:17.290
[ Sighs ]

35:17.290 --> 35:19.500
That's what I get
for making plans.

35:19.500 --> 35:27.620
♪♪

35:27.620 --> 35:29.170
I'm sorry.
It's okay.

35:29.170 --> 35:31.290
[ Sobbing ]

35:31.290 --> 35:32.620
It's okay.

35:32.620 --> 35:34.620
♪♪

35:34.620 --> 35:35.830
It's okay.

35:35.830 --> 35:37.120
[ Sniffles ]

35:37.120 --> 35:40.290
♪♪

35:45.120 --> 35:52.040
♪♪

35:52.040 --> 35:53.710
What are you doing?

35:53.710 --> 35:55.170
Oh, I'm sorry.

35:55.170 --> 35:57.170
I didn't realize
you were off your call.

35:57.170 --> 35:59.000
Hey, two-player.
Come on.

35:59.000 --> 36:01.380
All right.

36:01.380 --> 36:03.880
You may have beaten cancer
today, Gary,

36:03.880 --> 36:05.710
but you're not gonna
beat me.

36:05.710 --> 36:07.830
Correction --

36:07.830 --> 36:09.500
we beat cancer.

36:09.500 --> 36:12.670
[ Smacks leg ]

36:12.670 --> 36:14.170
Actually,
I beat cancer.

36:14.170 --> 36:15.830
You just got skinny
and bald.

36:15.830 --> 36:17.170
[ Imitating announcer ]
Oh, my God!

36:17.170 --> 36:18.540
The game
hasn't even started,

36:18.540 --> 36:21.710
and there's already a fight
breaking out.

36:21.710 --> 36:22.500
Whoa!
[ Normal voice ] Aah!

36:22.500 --> 36:24.170
[ Laughs ]

36:24.170 --> 36:26.040
I forgot, you were on the
pillow-fighting team at Harvard.

36:26.040 --> 36:27.330
No, I was on the wrestling team
at Harvard.

36:27.330 --> 36:28.500
No. You were the captain
of the pillow-fight--

36:28.500 --> 36:29.500
Oh, oh, what is this?

36:34.250 --> 36:36.540
[ Ivan & Alyosha's
"The Fold" plays ]

36:36.540 --> 36:43.040
♪♪

36:43.040 --> 36:49.420
♪♪

36:49.420 --> 36:50.750
[ Sighs ]

36:50.750 --> 36:53.380
♪♪

36:53.380 --> 36:57.040
♪ All the years
that you have wasted ♪

36:59.250 --> 37:00.880
♪ Now you want 'em all back ♪

37:00.880 --> 37:01.880
Regina: Pretty good.

37:01.880 --> 37:03.880
Right?

37:03.880 --> 37:05.420
Next time,
I'll call the super.

37:05.420 --> 37:06.920
♪ Long ago,
you stopped counting ♪

37:06.920 --> 37:08.710
Thank you.

37:08.710 --> 37:10.710
How are you feeling?

37:11.580 --> 37:13.920
♪ Because you couldn't
keep track ♪

37:13.920 --> 37:16.080
You know...

37:16.080 --> 37:19.250
I met the most
amazing man of my life

37:19.250 --> 37:20.960
when I was 30 seconds old.

37:22.750 --> 37:25.420
He doesn't get my life.

37:25.420 --> 37:27.920
And it's hard, you know,
'cause...

37:27.920 --> 37:30.250
♪ An oasis in the desert ♪

37:30.250 --> 37:34.250
...I wanted him
to be okay with this,

37:34.250 --> 37:35.580
and he's not.

37:35.580 --> 37:37.750
♪ Where the waters
run clear ♪

37:37.750 --> 37:39.420
[ Breathes deeply ]

37:39.420 --> 37:40.920
I've spent
my whole life...

37:40.920 --> 37:42.750
♪ And the only way
to see it ♪

37:42.750 --> 37:44.420
...proud
to be his son, and...

37:46.750 --> 37:47.750
♪ Is to believe
that it's there ♪

37:47.750 --> 37:50.080
I just want him to be proud
to be my dad.

37:50.080 --> 37:53.290
♪♪

37:53.290 --> 37:54.620
♪ Well, we all must fight
our battles ♪

37:54.620 --> 37:56.960
Here's the deal, babe.

37:56.960 --> 37:59.170
I get that you want him
to respect you.

37:59.170 --> 38:00.330
♪ No matter
where you came ♪

38:00.330 --> 38:02.120
But he's not gonna be able
to do that

38:02.120 --> 38:04.500
until you respect yourself.

38:04.500 --> 38:07.460
♪ So be done
with your excuses ♪
And you did that today.

38:07.460 --> 38:08.790
It'll come in time.

38:08.790 --> 38:10.960
♪♪

38:10.960 --> 38:13.000
I am so proud of you.

38:13.000 --> 38:14.290
♪ You're the only one
to blame ♪

38:14.290 --> 38:16.460
♪♪

38:16.460 --> 38:20.460
♪ Don't you fold ♪

38:20.460 --> 38:23.460
♪ When the mountain is high ♪

38:23.460 --> 38:26.620
♪ When the river is wide ♪

38:28.460 --> 38:32.620
♪ Don't you fold ♪

38:32.620 --> 38:35.330
♪ When you're out of your mind ♪

38:35.330 --> 38:38.330
♪ Yeah, when you're
walking around ♪

38:40.000 --> 38:44.500
♪ And all this time ♪

38:44.500 --> 38:47.670
♪ I was living a lie ♪

38:47.670 --> 38:50.500
♪ I was lost and petrified ♪

38:50.500 --> 38:52.000
♪ But I know that things ♪

38:52.000 --> 38:56.540
♪ Could change in time ♪

38:56.540 --> 38:59.330
♪ All the years
dreams can buy ♪

38:59.330 --> 39:02.000
♪ Between the heart
and the mind ♪

39:04.330 --> 39:08.500
♪ But don't you fold ♪

39:08.500 --> 39:11.330
♪ When the mountain is high ♪

39:11.330 --> 39:14.330
♪ When the river runs dry ♪

39:16.710 --> 39:17.880
♪ Don't you fold ♪

39:17.880 --> 39:19.040
Katherine:
It's too sticky.

39:19.040 --> 39:20.880
Theo:
Just needs more flour.

39:20.880 --> 39:22.540
♪ When you're
out of your mind ♪
Ah, perfect, perfect.

39:22.540 --> 39:24.250
Theo, you're allowed
to be my assistant.

39:24.250 --> 39:27.080
♪ When you're walking
the line ♪

39:27.080 --> 39:30.080
Best Chewbacca voice gets
to crank the dough first.

39:30.080 --> 39:31.380
Ready? Go.

39:31.380 --> 39:35.380
[ All imitating Chewbacca ]

39:35.380 --> 39:37.380
♪ When the river is wide ♪
Theo: Nice.

39:37.380 --> 39:38.710
What can I say?

39:38.710 --> 39:40.250
The Force is strong
in me.

39:40.250 --> 39:41.580
Yeah.

39:41.580 --> 39:43.040
♪ Don't you fold ♪
[ Laughs ]

39:43.040 --> 39:44.580
[ Cellphone buzzing ]

39:44.580 --> 39:45.710
Is this the call?

39:45.710 --> 39:47.380
Yeah.
Good luck.

39:47.380 --> 39:50.880
♪ Yeah, when you're
walking the line ♪

39:50.880 --> 39:52.920
Hi, Henry.

39:52.920 --> 39:54.920
Katherine, we would love
to make you partner.

39:54.920 --> 39:56.380
That is great.

39:56.380 --> 39:59.290
But we can't accept
your condition.

39:59.290 --> 40:02.420
♪ Don't you fold ♪
We need someone who is
fully committed to the job.

40:02.420 --> 40:04.750
Now, you think about it
tonight,

40:04.750 --> 40:05.620
let me know
in the morning?

40:05.620 --> 40:06.920
I will.

40:06.920 --> 40:08.420
Thanks.

40:08.420 --> 40:16.120
♪♪

40:16.120 --> 40:18.290
So, what'd he say?

40:18.290 --> 40:20.250
He said
I didn't make partner.

40:20.250 --> 40:25.750
♪♪

40:25.750 --> 40:27.580
Then why are you smiling?

40:27.580 --> 40:29.960
'Cause I just got
my life back.

40:29.960 --> 40:31.620
[ Imitating Chewbacca ]

40:31.620 --> 40:33.620
[ All imitating Chewbacca ]

40:33.620 --> 40:34.420
[ Laughter ]

40:34.420 --> 40:43.460
♪♪

40:43.460 --> 40:52.460
♪♪

40:52.460 --> 40:53.790
[ Sighs ]

40:53.790 --> 40:54.790
[ Cellphone beeps ]

40:54.790 --> 40:57.120
♪♪

40:57.120 --> 40:58.330
Hey, Keith.

40:58.330 --> 40:59.620
I thought about it.

41:01.460 --> 41:03.170
Let's do it.

41:03.170 --> 41:06.290
♪♪

41:07.290 --> 41:09.460
[ Cellphone buzzes ]

41:15.620 --> 41:21.500
♪♪

41:21.500 --> 41:27.830
♪♪

41:33.670 --> 41:36.500
[ Exhaling rhythmically ]

41:36.500 --> 41:37.500
[ Macklemore's "Can't Hold Us"
plays on radio ]

41:37.500 --> 41:39.000
